OL,6,FMr Makepeace said: "Immediately Mr
OL,7,FO'Hara felt a terrible pain and jumped
OL,8,Fback. He shouted, 'bloody hell' and
OL,9,Fexplained the immediate and intense
OL,10,Fpain, but the nurse reassured him it
OL,11,Fwas not an uncommon, bad reaction and
OL,12,Fit was nothing to be concerned about.
OL,14,F"However, from that point forward, the
OL,15,Fnurse began to noticeably speed up his
OL,16,Fdeparture, packing up his equipment
OL,17,Fand leaving the premises in something
OL,18,Fof a rush, telling Mr O'Hara not to
OL,19,Fworry about his stinging arm as the
OL,20,Fpain would pass in time."
