OL,6,FMr Makepeace said: "Mr Kwan's
OL,7,Fknowledge of poisons, his extensive
OL,8,Fresearch and acquired expertise means
OL,9,Fhe cannot have been ignorant of the
OL,10,Flife-threatening nature of the assault
OL,11,Fhe was perpetrating."
OL,13,FThe court was told analysis by Dr
OL,14,FSteven Emmett, the Chief Medical
OL,15,FOfficer at the Defence Science and
OL,16,FTechnology Laboratories, operated as
OL,17,Fpart of the Ministry of Defence, found
OL,18,Fa chemical called iodomethane was a
OL,19,F"viable candidate" for the poison
OL,20,Finjected into Mr O'Hara.
